The paper presents an automatic approach for parcellating histological sections of the human brain using convolutional neural networks. This involves combining topological information from probabilistic atlases with texture features learned from high-resolution cell-body stained images. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves image analysis and classification. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
